# Research Briefing

**Goal:** Prove or make substantial progress toward an inverse theorem for η-extremal configurations in F_p^r.

Specifically: if A is a set of nonzero vectors in F_p^r such that the multiset {v^{p-1} : v in A} is zero-sum-free for lengths <= p, and |A| = 9·2^{r-3} - 1 (the conjectured maximum), prove that A must have the recursive product structure A = {(0,v) : v in B} ∪ {(1,v) : v in B} ∪ {e_1} for some η-extremal set B in F_p^{r-1}.

Equivalently: prove that any maximal zero-sum-free set decomposes as a doubled-plus-e1 of a maximal set in one lower dimension.

If the full inverse theorem is too hard, prove it for r=4 and p=3 (where alpha(4)=17 is verified computationally and the set has only 80 candidate vectors).

